gujarati.context:
Here is the translation:

Charu rangedan range bharya, vali bharriyan motali maat;
Maharaja betha mailiyee, jan joii rahya valli vaat.

After that I will not take, the matter of my own hands; 
I will wait and see what will happen by itself; 

Worshiping well done at the time it was done, that too has become auspicious to me.

Given couplet:

"Given to the saint, take worship you with devotion;
Like a coral, sandalwood, and jasmine, worship is established in its proper way."

Here is the translation:

Do this playful thing with Hari, accept it in your heart; 
Do this playful thing in worldly affairs, then something will be brief.
